Replacing NA Values¶

In [731]:
df['Initial']=0
for i in df:
    df['Initial']=df.Name.str.extract('([A-Za-z]+)\.') #lets extract the Salutations

A majority of the children under 5 were saved in the accident

The oldest passenger saved was 80. the next oldest passenger who survived was somewhere between 60-65. Props to that guy for surviving.

20-25 and 30-35 saw the most survivors. However, the most deaths seen was in the 30-35 age group. Probably because that was close to the mean age. Also because maybe those people were stalwart and sacrificed themselves to save others. I'm gonna go with the latter.

Sibling Analysis¶

SibSp shows how many siblings/spouses the person was travelling with. Siblings include brother, sister, step sister, step brother, and step sister.

Obviously, spouse is referring to a husband or wife

In [756]:

In [757]:
f,ax=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(20,8))
sns.barplot('SibSp','Survived',data=df,ax=ax[0])
ax[0].set_title('SibSp vs Survived')
sns.factorplot('SibSp','Survived',data=df,ax=ax[1])
ax[1].set_title('SibSp vs Survived')
plt.close(2)
plt.show()

  1. The people with a large number of siblings/family members had an extremely low survival rate.

  2. The best spot to be was have 1-2 siblings or spouse. A likely combination would be husband wife and a child.

  3. Someone with just one sibling/spouse with them had the highest survival chances. Experiencing this disaster with a sibling and friend is likely what pushed some of these people to survive.

In [836]:
# defining our own confusion matrix function
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
def my_confusion_matrix(y, y_hat):
    cm = confusion_matrix(y, y_hat)
    TN, FP, FN, TP = cm[0,0], cm[0,1], cm[1,0], cm[1,1]
    accuracy = round((TP+TN) / (TP+ FP+ FN+ TN) ,2)
    precision = round( TP / (TP+FP),2)
    recall = round( TP / (TP+FN),2)
    cm_labled = pd.DataFrame(cm, index=['Actual : 0 ','Actual : 1'], columns=['Predict : 0','Predict :1 '])
    print('\n')
    print('Accuracy = {}'.format(accuracy))
    print('Precision = {}'.format(precision))
    print('Recall = {}'.format(recall))
    print("-----------------------------------------")
    return cm_labled
